@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Lightit" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, the game requires a 68020(+)
Amiga with Workbench 2.0 or higher.

                             How to play?

  The game is played on an hexagonally shaped game board filled
with lightbulbs that are either lit or unlit. The idea is to switch
on all the lightbulbs on the board.

  To play, simply click on a lightbulb, this will switch on or off
all the lightbulbs located on the same row and diagonally from
where that lightbulb is located. Note that a lightbulb is 'on' if
it is white and 'off' when it is black (this is assuming, of course,
that black and white on your Workbench palette are respectively
colour 1 and 2...). When you complete a game board, Lightit will
display how many moves you made, and then will display a new, more
complex game board, and so on...

  If you find that the game is too easy to play, you can play with
the 'Harder' game by clicking on the 'Easy/Harder Game' button...

  You can restart a game board anytime, by clicking on the
'Restart' button. But note that the number of moves you have made
will accumulate until you complete the game board.

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

